rComments: He is one of the best professors UofT can offer. He makes sure that everyone in the class understands. If students are not good at topic he explains again and again. It is an exciting course.

Prof Prodic is a nice person, but his course administration is always terrible. He posts homework in a very inconsistent form - pdf, announcements, and even emails. In the tests, he may change his paper multiple times to drive you nuts, and may not even test on the "key" topics he has emphasised in class. Lastly, he is a tough grader

Prof Prodic is very helpful in not only academic consultancy, but also conversations about career and life. He is passionate about cultivating the right engineering mindset for students. He even bought us food and drinks after the final exam
